rComments: Awesome prof and has an interest in a really unique field--food geographies.

All I have to say is she is VERY HARD. I got a B+, and I worked extremely hard for that when usually I don't have to. She is very inflexible, strict, and a very hard marker. Her lectures and content where interesting but her personality killed it for me. She is also VERY picky when it comes to answering exam questions.

Wonderful professor, love Prof Tanaka! Although it wasn't a mandatory course for any of my majors, I'm so glad to have taken a D-level elective course with her. She is very engaging with what she teaches, a fair marker, approachable and friendly! Definitely go to her office hours if you need to. Oh, and not to mention, she is gorgeous!

Amazing professor, who may have potentially changed my life. She is a fair grader, and knows how to pick articles that both engage the reader and well, don't bore us to death. She might seem intimidating at first, but she is in fact, really nice. Take a class with her for sure!

I don't understand these other posters are saying. She seems intimidating, but she is not. If you go to her office hours, and talk to her a little bit, she is very friendly. She is engaging, and helpful, like all professors should be. She is also a considerably fair marker. (Do the readings, you're good to go.)
Really nice prof. I wish I had her for my other courses as well. Gives good examples and goes straight to the point. Super nice if you approach her in office hours.

I really liked this class and thought she did a great job teaching it. Let's face it - learning about research methods is nobody's cup of tea. It takes talent to make something so boring engaging and I hope to take classes with her again.

This professor is extremely hard. She does not care about her students and does not help at all. If you ask her for help over email, she says come to her office hours. And when you go to her office hours, she indirectly tells you to figure things out on your own. Although i got a B- in her class, i worked so hard, and i definately deserved better.
